Governor Babagana Zulum of Borno State on Monday inaugurated two new roads measuring a total of 5.8 kilometres in Maiduguri, the state capital. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the roads are the 2.1km Zannari Road and drain; rehabilitated 626m Sheikh Abba Aji Road, both in London-Ciki, and the 3.1km Bintu-Sugar Road and drain in Ngomari. Speaking at the event, Zulum said that the project was a fulfilment of his campaign promise to the people. Earlier, the Chairman of the stateâ€™s roads maintenance agency, Sadu Abdullahi, said the Zulum administration constructed 35 roads across the state in the past three years. (NAN) 